OL,7,FShadow home secretary Chris Philp said
OL,8,FLabour was "playing catch-up" with
OL,9,FConservative proposals to toughen
OL,10,Findefinite leave to remain rules.
OL,12,FBut he said the plans were a "watered-
OL,13,Fdown copy" of his party's plans, which
OL,14,Fwent further by pledging to also end
OL,15,Fautomatic citizenship routes, put an
OL,16,Fannual cap on legal migration and not
OL,17,Frenew visas for the unemployed or
OL,18,Fthose in low-paid jobs.
